@node Use with Linux STREAMS
@section Use with Linux STREAMS
@cindex use with linux fast-streams

The @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package was originally part of the @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} base
package, @file{streams}.  The purpose for separating the package was originally to support both
@cite{LiS} and @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} until such time as @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} was a suitable
production replacement for @cite{LiS}.  With release @b{streams-@value{VERSION_STREAMS}}, @cite{Linux
Fast-STREAMS} is a far superior production replacement for @cite{LiS} and @cite{LiS} is now
deprecated.  Although, at one time, the @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package worked with @cite{LiS},
it is no longer supported on @cite{LiS} and is only tested and validated for @cite{Linux
Fast-STREAMS}.  Even when it was supported, @cite{LiS} has so many bugs, deficiencies and
incompatibilities in the Stream head, that it was not possible to obtain usable compatibility in
conjunction with @cite{LiS}.  @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} does not have these problems.

@node Use with Linux Fast-STREAMS
@section Use with Linux Fast-STREAMS
@cindex use with linux fast-streams

The @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package functions much better with the @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS}
implementation with which it was originally intended to function.  @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS}
provides a superset of the capabilities of @cite{SVR 4.2 MP} intended to provide compatibility
across as many mainstream @cite{UNIX} implementations of @dfn{STREAMS} as possible.  Also,
@cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} does not have the bugs, races, deficiencies, and other difficulties
present in the @cite{LiS} package.@footnote{@cite{The OpenSS7 Project} really has no vested interest
in promoting @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} over @cite{LiS}.  The project uses @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS}
instead of @cite{LiS} based on technical merit alone.  @cite{The OpenSS7 Project} has released both
@cite{LiS} and @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} packages and has provided support for both packages up
until the production release of @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS}.  Many of the @cite{OpenSS7 Project}
@dfn{STREAMS} modules and drivers will still run under @cite{LiS}, albeit with far less performance
far poorer conformance to standards, and the all too frequent kernel crashes experienced with
@cite{LiS}.}


