@node Mentat Portable Streams (MPS) Utility Functions
@subsubsection Mentat Portable Streams (MPS) Utility Functions

The @cite{Mentat Portable Streams (MPS)} utility functions are important because they exist on many
@cite{UNIX} systems.  @cite{AIX}, @cite{HP-UX}, @cite{OSF/1.2} and @cite{Mac OpenTransport} are
based on @cite{MPS}.  Almost all variants use the @cite{Mentat} TCP/IP implementations, and
therefore have implementations of many of these functions internally if not exposed.  @cite{AIX},
@cite{OSF/1.2} and especially @cite{Mac OpenTransport} expose and document most (if not all) of
these functions.   The @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package supports all of these
functions.@footnote{Lately the @cite{OpenSS7 Project} has moved away from using OpenSS7 defined
helper functions and move toward using the MPS functions instead.  Many of the OpenSS7 utilities
predate the compatibility modules and were developed in ignorance of the existing helper functions
defined by Mentat and Sun.  As such, most OpenSS7 communications protocol stacks require this module
to be present on the system.}

